In this episode of the program and its structure is defined in the database.
The name of the application database:  Dbhabh

1 - used in database tables:

1.TbAppInfo

2.TbUser

3.TBMessage

4.TbLike

5.TbCommand

6.TbContact


1 - 1: TbAppInfo

The fields used in this table are as follows: 

1-1-1: InfoId ([numeric](18, 0) IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL)
1-1-2: InfoAppName ([nvarchar](100) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-1-3: InfoAppVersion ([nvarchar](10) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS )
1-1-4: InfoEmail ([nvarchar](100) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS )
1-1-5: InfoWebSite ([nvarchar](100) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS )


Description:
This table is stored in the program itself Information.

---------

1-2 : TbUser

In the table of users that are members of the program is maintained.

1-2-1: UserID ([numeric](18, 0) IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL)
1-2-2: UserName ([nvarchar](100) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-2-3: UserEmail ([nvarchar](100) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-2-4: UserDateJoin ([nvarchar](10) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-2-5: UserPicture ([nvarchar](100) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)


Description:

1-2-1 : User identification information, including name and family
1-2-2: Email address of the user
1-2-3: Date of user registration 
1-2-4: Users select their picture and address in this field can be stored images in this section.

----------

1-3 : TbMessage

This table is stored in text messages sent from the user.

1-3-1: MessageId ([numeric](18, 0) IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL)
1-3-2: MessageUserId ([numeric](18) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-3-3: MessageMessage ([nvarchar](300) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-3-4: MessageDate ([nvarchar](10) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)

Description:

1-3-2: The user ID of the person who sent the text messages are stored.
1-3-3: Text messages sent from users that the maximum is 300 characters.
1-3-4: date to send text messages from users


1-4: TbLike

Likes do the members of any text messages are stored in this section

1-4-1: LikeId ([numeric](18, 0) IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL)
1-4-2: LikeMessageId ([numeric](18) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-4-3: LikeUserId ([numeric](18) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)

Description:

1-4-2: Liked the text messages ID
1-4-3: The user ID that made Likes

------------

1-5: TbCommand

Member Comments about outgoing text messages are stored in this table.

1-5-1: CommandId ([numeric](18, 0) IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL)
1-5-2: CommandUserID ([numeric](18) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-5-3: CommandMessageID ([numeric](18) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-5-4: CommandCommand ([nvarchar](100) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-5-5: CommandDate ([nvarchar](20) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)


Description:

1-5-2: Comments userId who has
1-5-3: text messages ID in which the comment was made
1-5-4: Comment text sent from a user
1-5-5: Date and Time  post comments



And


1-6: TbContact

In this table, users can  comments, criticisms, questions for the us to send your suggestions


1-6-1: ContactID ([numeric](18, 0) IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL)
1-6-2: ContaxtUserId ([numeric](18) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-6-3: ContaxtMessage ([nvarchar](1000) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-6-4: ContactDate ([nvarchar](20) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS)
1-6-5: ContactState ([numeric](1) COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS -   (State (seen or unseen))



------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To extract the information needed to write a view

For example:

1- All comments have been posted on text messageID=2


SELECT     dbo.TbMessage.MessageId, dbo.TbMessage.MessageMessage, dbo.TbUser.UserName, dbo.TbCommand.CommandCommand
FROM         dbo.TbCommand INNER JOIN
                      dbo.TbMessage ON dbo.TbCommand.CommandMessageId = dbo.TbMessage.MessageId INNER JOIN
                      dbo.TbUser ON dbo.TbCommand.CommandId = dbo.TbUser.UserId
WHERE     (dbo.TbMessage.MessageId = 2)



2- All Like Posted On text Message Id=1





SELECT     dbo.TbMessage.MessageId, dbo.TbMessage.MessageMessage, dbo.TbUser.UserName, dbo.TbUser.UserId
FROM         dbo.TbMessage INNER JOIN
                      dbo.TbLike ON dbo.TbMessage.MessageId = dbo.TbLike.LikeMessageId INNER JOIN
                      dbo.TbUser ON dbo.TbLike.LikeUserId = dbo.TbUser.UserId
WHERE     (dbo.TbMessage.MessageId = 1)





3- Select All Text Message Post By UserId=2

SELECT     dbo.TbMessage.MessageUserId, dbo.TbUser.UserName, dbo.TbMessage.MessageMessage
FROM         dbo.TbUser INNER JOIN
                      dbo.TbMessage ON dbo.TbUser.UserId = dbo.TbMessage.MessageUserId
WHERE     (dbo.TbMessage.MessageUserId = 2)


